---
import BadgeShine from "@/components/BadgeShine.astro";
import Button from "@/components/Button.astro";
import Github from "@/components/logos/Github.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import logos from "@/logos";

const technologies = [
  logos.REACT,
  logos.TYPESCRIPT,
  logos.TAILWIND,
  logos.VITE,
  logos.NestJS,
  logos.Prisma
]

const images = [
  "/portfolio-web/images/user_table_gallery/login.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/user_table_gallery/user_view.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/user_table_gallery/user_creation.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/user_table_gallery/excel_management.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/user_table_gallery/direction_management.webp"
]
---

<Layout title="User Administration Table" desc="Details about the User Admin. Table project!">
  <section class="pt-40 pb-40 w-full md:w-9/12 mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-5 underline">ConnectDesk</h1>
    
    <nav class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-y-5 w-fit gap-x-4 text-wrap mb-5">
      <BadgeShine class="flex flex-row gap-x-2" href="https://github.com/JoelFaldin/React-User-Administration-Frontend">
        <Github class="size-6" />
        Frontend
      </BadgeShine>
      <BadgeShine class="flex flex-row gap-x-2" href="https://github.com/JoelFaldin/React-User-Administration-Backend">
        <Github class="size-6" />
        Backend
      </BadgeShine>
    </nav>

    <article class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-x-10 pb-14">
      <section class="w-full lg:w-2/5 text-wrap flex flex-col gap-y-2">
        <p>I worked on this project in an internship I had in january 2024!</p>
        <p>The goal was to create a <span class="text-cyan-500">web application</span> that could display information about the users (e.g. their phone number and email address), making it accesible to everyone.</p>
        <p>When I started the project, I wanted to use <a href="https://tanstack.com/table/latest" class="text-cyan-500 hover:underline">TanStack Table</a> to handle all of the data in the frontend, but then they asked me to use querys to get the data. It was too late to change everything, so I used TanStackTable without all of its benefits. ðŸ˜¢</p>
        <p>Something interesting I had to implement was a way to upload and download an <span class="text-cyan-500">excel file</span>, and save its data to the database. You can see an image of it below!</p>
        <p>Originally, I built this project using JavaScript and TypeScript, but after some time I migrated it to TypeScript and <a href="https://nestjs.com/" class="text-cyan-500 hover:underline">NestJS</a> and <a href="https://www.prisma.io/" class="text-cyan-500 hover:underline">Prisma</a>.</p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-xl">Technologies used:</p>

        <ul class="flex gap-x-4 flex-row mt-2 mb-2">
          {
            technologies.map(logo => (
              <li>
                <logo.icon class="size-8" />
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section class="w-3/5">
        <img
          src="/portfolio-web/images/user_admin_screenshot.webp"
          alt="Main view of the User Administration project"
          height="350"
          width="700"
          class="shadow-xl border border-cyan-500 h-72 w-auto md:h-[350px] min-w-fit"
        >
      </section>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">More images:</h2>

      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 xl:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
        {
          images.map(pic => (
            <img
              src={pic}
              height="300"
              width="600"
              class="w-fit shadow-2xl"
              alt="Image examples of the React User Administration project"
            />
          ))
        }
      </section>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>